 Educational Background



Bachelor's Degree in Law 
Class of 1991 


The Hebrew University of Jerusalem

                  The Hebrew University of Jerusalem is Israel's second oldest university established in 1918, 30 years before the State of Israel. The Hebrew University has three campuses in Jerusalem and one in Rehovot. The world's largest Jewish studies library is located on its Edmond J. Safra Givat Ram campus.                





 Career History



Partner

                                    Current                


Meretzki-Tavor






Vice Chairman-National Council

                                    Current                


Israel Bar Association







 Boards & Committees



Corporate Boards ▾




Member, Board of Directors

                    2003 - Current                  


Pluristem Therapeutics Inc.

                    Pluristem Therapeutics, Inc. is a biotechnology company engages in the provision of cell therapy development. It focuses on cell therapies for the treatment of diseases such as muscle injury, acute radiation syndrome, pulmonary arterial hypertension and others. Its products include PLacental eXpanded, PLX-PAD, and PLX-R18. The company was founded by Doron Shorrer on May 11, 2001 and is headquartered in Haifa, Israel.                  




Director

                    Prior                  


The Israel Electric Corp. Ltd.

                    Israel Electric Corp. Ltd. generates, transmits, sells and distributes electricity. It offers its services to the households, industrial, public and commercial buildings, and bulk water pumping and agriculture. The company was founded on March 29, 1923 and is headquartered in Haifa, Israel.                  




Director

                    Prior                  


Israel Electric Co.






